    "summary": "I am currently the EMEA Financial controller for Omron Management Center Europe which is a shared service center. I am leading and developing the Financial control team.  I am currently responsible for 7 people within the Financial control team which performs the closing for 3 business industries and 50 entities. \n\nFormer Experienced Senior Associate/ Junior Manager at PwC Amsterdam in the Consumer Industrial Products & Services (CIPS) Department. At PwC, I audited large multi-national companies both under IFRS, US GAAP (incl. SOX testing) & Dutch GAAP. I worked on various companies listed on the NYSE. I was responsible for overall project management, coaching, reviewing, coordination, controls assessment & financial statement review. +/- 10 people reported directly to me throughout the year on my engagements and I was also responsible for outsourcing work to our service delivery centres in Netherlands, Poland, India & South Africa and coaching them who then also reported to me.\n\nI have experience in multiple industries including retail, production, energy, automotive, technology and mining.",
